Package game.actors

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    ActorSpawn
    An interface that represents spawning an actor.
    Attackable
    An interface for objects that can be attacked by actors in the game.
    Monologue
    Interface that allows an actor to have a monologue conversation.
    Respawnable
    The Respawnable interface defines the contract for objects that can be respawned in a game.

    A Red Wolf actor that has the ability to be spawned.
    Respawner
    The Respawner class is responsible for handling player respawning and map reset operations.
    Trader
    Class representing a trader actor.
    Traveller

    WanderingUndead
